<%# Phase 27 v2 spec 05 — `/games` is a single shelves-by-letter
    layout. The display-mode switcher and the three per-mode partials
    (`_grid_mode` / `_list_mode` / `_shelves_by_letter_mode`) are gone;
    the page renders one stack of shelves top-to-bottom:

      1. Page title `games` + `[+]`.
      2. Filter row (spec 06 reworks the row's internal layout).
      3. Recently-played shelf (only when at least one game has
         `played_at` set).
      4. Hairline.
      5. Genres outer shelf (one sub-shelf per non-empty genre, short
         heading labels per `GenresHelper#genre_short_name`).
      6. Hairline.
      7. Bundles outer shelf (one tile per non-empty bundle, alphabetical;
         clicking a tile opens the bundles-modal pane).
      8. Hairline.
      9. Letter shelves (one shelf per non-empty letter A..Z, then
         `#` bucket at the end if non-empty).

    Phase 27 follow-up (2026-05-17) — the legacy top-of-page "bundles"
    shelf (10 most-recent bundles) was merged into the Bundles outer
    shelf below; they were two views onto the same model and the
    Collection→Bundle consolidation made the duplication redundant.

    Phase 27 v2 spec 06 — the listing partition (shelves 3–10 above)
    is wrapped in `<turbo-frame id="games_listing">` so the
    `games-filter` Stimulus controller can re-fetch the frame on
    chip toggle without re-rendering the filter row itself or
    triggering a full page navigation.

    Each shelf carries the `steam-shelf` Stimulus controller for
    drag-scroll + mouse-wheel-to-horizontal scroll, with the project's
    themed slim scrollbar (6 px on both axes — see the global
    `::-webkit-scrollbar` rules in `app/assets/tailwind/application.css`).

    Phase 14 §1 polish (2026-05-10) — the inline IGDB type-ahead
    `_add_form` partial was retired. The H1 carries a `[+]`
    bracketed link that opens the layout-level IGDB-search modal
    (`shared/_igdb_search_modal`). 2026-05-17 — the previous global
    `i` keybind was removed in the legacy-keyboard-shortcut sweep;
    the `[+]` link is now the only entry point. %>
<% content_for(:title, "games") %>

<%# 2026-05-17 polish (revised) — `/games` shares one horizontal column
    with the rest of the page. The chrome wrapper (`<main>`) in
    `application.html.erb` already carries the canonical 12 px
    horizontal padding; this view does NOT introduce its own
    `max-width` clamp or viewport break-out. Title row, filter row,
    and shelves Turbo Frame all sit inside the same content container
    so their left and right edges line up with the navbar nav links
    (and the footer copy) — i.e. 12 px from each viewport edge.

    The previous `max-width: 1100px` wrapper around the title + filter
    band, plus the `.games-shelves-fullwidth` viewport break-out
    around the shelves frame, were removed in favor of this single
    aligned column. Per-shelf horizontal scroll on overflow is
    unchanged — each `.shelf` row keeps its own `overflow-x: auto`. %>
<div>
  <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 6px;">
    <div class="dot-list">
      <h1>games</h1>
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(
            label: "+",
            href: "#",
            data: {
              controller: "modal-trigger",
              action: "click->modal-trigger#open",
              modal_trigger_target_id_value: "igdb-search-modal"
            }
          )) %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Phase 27 v2 spec 06 — single compact filter band. All chips
      default to CHECKED; URL `/games` (no `?filters=`) means "full
      list". The Stimulus controller mounted on the row itself manages
      chip toggles, the cascade, and the Turbo Frame refresh. The
      row stays OUTSIDE the `games_listing` frame so it does not
      re-render per chip click. The row uses `justify-content:
      space-between` internally so the left (status + ownership) chip
      group sits flush against the content container's left edge and
      the right (platform) chip group sits flush against its right
      edge — aligning with the navbar / footer chrome. %>
  <%= render Games::FilterRowComponent.new(
        checked_tokens:         @checked_tokens,
        request_path:           games_path
      ) %>

  <%# Phase 27 v2 spec 06 — Turbo Frame wraps the listing partition.
      Filter chip clicks point the frame at the new URL via Stimulus;
      the frame fetches and morphs in the new contents without a full
      navigation. The frame id (`games_listing`) is declared in the
      FilterRowComponent's `data-games-filter-frame-id-value` for the
      controller to target — frame lookup is by id, so the frame may
      live anywhere in the document as long as the id is unique. %>
  <%= turbo_frame_tag "games_listing" do %>
    <% has_any_content = @recently_played.any? ||
                         @genres_for_shelf.any? || @bundles_for_shelf.any? ||
                         @letter_buckets.any? %>

    <% if has_any_content %>
      <% if @recently_played.any? %>
        <%= render(Games::ShelfComponent.new(
              heading: "recently played",
              show_count: false,
              heading_level: :h2,
              row_gap: "8px"
            )) do %>
          <% @recently_played.each do |game| %>
            <%= render(Games::GameTileComponent.new(game: game, variant: :grid)) %>
          <% end %>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>

      <%# Phase 27 §01c-v2 — Genres outer shelf. One sub-shelf per non-
          empty genre, alphabetical. Empty buckets hidden. %>
      <% if @genres_for_shelf.any? %>
        <hr class="hairline">
        <%= render "games/genres_shelf", genres: @genres_for_shelf %>
      <% end %>

      <%# Bundles outer shelf — one tile per non-empty bundle. %>
      <% if @bundles_for_shelf.any? %>
        <hr class="hairline">
        <%= render "games/bundles_for_shelf", bundles: @bundles_for_shelf %>
      <% end %>

      <%# Phase 27 v2 spec 05 — Letter shelves. One `<section>` per non-
          empty letter; `#` bucket renders LAST when present. %>
      <% if @letter_buckets.any? %>
        <hr class="hairline">
        <%= render "games/letter_shelves", buckets: @letter_buckets %>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>
